TY  - JOUR
TI  - Large Language Models for Automated Literature Review: A Systematic Analysis
AU  - Zhang, Wei
AU  - Li, Ming
AU  - Chen, Jing
PY  - 2024
AB  - This paper presents a systematic analysis of large language models applied to automated literature review tasks. We evaluate the effectiveness of different LLM architectures in generating citation-grounded summaries from academic abstracts. Our experiments demonstrate that structured prompting with evidence IDs significantly reduces hallucination compared to free-form generation. The results show that GPT-4 and Claude models achieve the highest accuracy in evidence extraction, while smaller models struggle with maintaining citation fidelity across large document sets.
JO  - Journal of Artificial Intelligence Research
DO  - 10.1613/jair.2024.001
